5:
I see. So no one was gravely injured
while fleeing the settlement.
8:
Thank you for telling me, Addie. Can
I leave the rest to you?
11:
S-sure! You know I've got your back!
We can do this!
14:
Was that really Addie? I almost
didn't recognize her. I guess love
really does chang—
21:
I'm in agreement with Alk and the
others! We must stop the troops
headed to the Vesta settlement!
24:
Attacking them now will only lead to
needless bloodshed. I cannot allow
such a—
28:
I can't change a decision that's
already been made. It's out of my
hands, Keira.
33: Then I refuse to follow such orders!
37:
I'm pretty sure that counts as a
rebellion...
49:
Refusing our orders would only
disrupt the trust the Guild Knights
have built up within Palpebra.
59:
Here, this is your portion. Pur Lilie
and Sharon will be helping too... I
also have some for you, Captain.
73:
Once we submit the paperwork, the
Vesta will be given temporary
residency status for the duration of
the application process.
75:
Their illegal occupation of the land
will then be considered a civil
matter, leaving our hands tied.
82:
All this is going to do is buy us some
time, you know.
88:
That's all right. I'm sure our friends
will handle the rest.
93:
...I apologize. I should have been
looking for a solution, but instead I
let my emotions get the better of
me...
98:
You're the one who provided us with
this intel. If it weren't for you, I
couldn't have made these
preparations.
100:
Just make sure you keep your
temper in check next time. Until
then, we have work to do. Isn't that
right, Keira?
110:
Hey, I'd hate to interrupt your little
lover's chat, but—
119:
I don't think you need to worry about
buying time.
122:
Those friends of yours turned out to
be more reckless than I thought.
131:
Anyway, it sounds like they want our
help with a little "monster hunt."
133:
We're going to show the world what
the Guild Knights are REALLY
capable of. This is a lot bigger than
guard duty.
135:
That being said, we'll have a lot
more work on our hands. You okay
with that?
144: ...Would it kill you to hesitate a little?
149:
Ah, could I have you both work on
those residency applications just in
case? Always good to have a
backup plan.
160:
Well? Sounds like we did our part
quite nicely, don't you think?
163:
Uh... "We"? Sounds like you just
pushed everything onto Finn and
Keira.
167:
A superior is supposed to give their
subordinates work. It's all part of the
job.
172:
Yes, it would be very bad if one
person were to try to do everything...
177: Ah, r-right. I'll keep that in mind.
180: Still, are you sure this is okay?
189:
I'm just... worried. We didn't put the
Guild Knights in a bad position, did
we?
193:
Nah, if anything, I'd say it improved
our standing.
196:
We were able to show off both the
academy's firepower as well as our
own. More than a few people are
happy with that outcome.
198:
After all, why form the Guild Knights
and a magic academy if you're not
going to use them?
202:
That doesn't really help you guys on
the frontlines though...
206:
Yeah, well, a lot of us grunts dream
of glory and what-not.
210:
Might as well actually live out those
dreams. I'd say that leaves everyone
happy, wouldn't you?
212:
Besides, if I side with Kugala all the
time, the other groups might get
jealous...
220:
You say that now, but I hope you're
ready to throw your hat in the ring.
227:
Do you really think a little cake is
enough to repay the debt you owe
me now?
230:
We'll be working together for a long,
long time... Hope you're ready.
233:
Anyway, thanks for the cake. It sure
was good.
238:
This fiasco is really gonna cost us,
huh...
241: Would you like me to deal with him?
249:
You do realize Regis installed
surveillance cameras here, correct?
I have eyes and ears everywhere.
252:
It seems that man noticed my
shikigami as well. He's a crafty one,
that's for sure.
256: ...Yeah, but I think we'll be fine.
259:
Like he said, we do owe him a great
debt. It'd be wrong to weasel our
way out of paying him back.
262:
He might not always be the most
upstanding guy, but we couldn't
have saved the Vesta without him.
266: We will be fine, Suizen. Do not worry.
271:
...Fine. If you're both going to be like
that, I can't really object.
275:
You sure can't, boy. Learn to trust
your elders a little, would you?
280:
Haha, silly old me. I forgot my stuff.
Anyway, I'll be off.
284: He's a crafty one, all right...
